ese Navy cruisers. All 40 crew survived.<ref name=\"Imperial cruisers\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Elsa|1928|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Indian Ocean Raid|Operation C]]: The tanker was shelled and sunk in the [[Bay of Bengal]] {{convert|35|nmi|km}} east of [[Cuttack]], [[Orissa, India|Orissa]], [[British India|India]] by two [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] cruisers with the loss of one of her 30 crew.<ref name=Elsa>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/elsa.html |title= M/T Elsa |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=12 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Exmoor|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States}}\n|desc=World War II:  [[Indian Ocean Raid|Operation C]]: The cargo ship was shelled and sunk in the [[Bay of Bengal]] ({{coord|19|53|N|86|30|E}})  by {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Kumano||2}} and {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Suzuya|1934|2}} and {{ship|Japanese destroyer|Shirakumo|1927|2}} (all {{navy|Empire of Japan}}).<ref name=\"combinedfleet.com\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Gandara|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Indian Ocean Raid|Operation C]]: The cargo ship was shelled in the [[Bay of Bengal]]  by {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Mikuma||2}} and {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Mogami|1934|2}} and torpedoed by {{ship|Japanese destroyer|Amagiri|1930|2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}) and sunk while towing {{SS|Dardanus||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}).<ref name=\"Imperial cruisers\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ganges|1930|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Indian Ocean Raid|Operation C]]: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Bay of Bengal]] 25 miles south of Vizagapatam by floatplanes from {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Ch\u014dkai||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}).<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Chokai_t.htm |title=Imperial cruisers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=6 April 2014}}</ref> Fif