rican college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season  \n|sport        =Basketball  \n|year         =1912-13  \n|prev_year    =1911\u201312  \n|next_year    =1913\u201314  \n|team         =Kansas Jayhawks  \n|image        =  \n|image_size   =  \n|conference   =Missouri Valley Intercollegiate Athletic Association  \n|division     =  \n|short_conf   =MVIAA  \n|CoachRank    =  \n|APRank       =  \n|record       =16-6\n|conf_record  =8-3 \n|head_coach   =[[W.O. Hamilton]]  \n|hc_year      = 4th  \n| captain      =   \n| mvp          =   \n|asst_coach1  =  \n|asst_coach2  =  \n|asst_coach3  =  \n|stadium      =[[Robinson Gymnasium]]  \n|champion     =\n|bowl         =  \n|bowl_result  =\n}}\nThe '''1912\u201313 Kansas Jayhawks men's basketball team''' represented the [[University of Kansas]] during the 1912-13 college men's basketball season. They were coached by [[W. O. Hamilton]] who was in his 3rd year as head coach.\n\n==Roster==\n*Walter Boehm\n*Loren Brown\n*Ray Dunmire\n*Charles Greenless\n*Ora Hite\n*Ralph Sproull\n*Arthur Weaver\n<ref name = \"KU Media Guide\">[http://sidearm.sites.s3.amazonaws.com/kuathletics.com/documents/2014/10/9/201415_KU_mbb_media_guide.pdf 2014-15 Kansas Jayhawks men's basketball media guide]. Retrieved 2015-May-22.</ref>\n\n==Schedule and results==\nThis schedule is incomplete.\n{{CBB schedule start\n| time      = \n| rank      = \n| tv        = \n| gamehighs =\n| attend    =\n}}\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date         = January 16\n| time         = \n| w/l          = w\n| nonconf      = yes\n| away         = \n| neutral      = \n| rank         = \n| opponent     = [[Haskell Indian Nations Fighting Indians|Haskell Indian Nations]]\n| opprank      = \n| site_stadium = [[Robinson Gymnasium]]\n| site_cityst  = [[Lawrence, Kansas|Lawrence, KS]]\n| gamename     = \n| tv           = \n| highscorer   =\n| points       =\n| highrebounder=\n| rebounds     =\n| highassister =\n| assists      =\n| score        = 56&ndash;27\n| overtime     = 