s]]\n*[[Cory Silverberg]]*\n*[[Paco Ignacio Taibo II]]\n*[[\u00c1ngela Vallvey]] \n*[[Howard Zinn]]*\n{{Col-break}}\n{{Col-end}}\n{{small |* Indicates authors whose work was published in Spanish translation}}\n\n===Triangle Square Books for Young Readers===\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n*[[Julia Alvarez]]\n*Ali Berman\n*[[Tamara Bower]]\n*[[Seymour Chwast]] \n*Meryl Danziger\n*[[Jared Diamond]]\n{{Col-break}}\n*[[Ariel Dorfman]]\n*Morten D\u00fcrr\n*[[Marcus Ewert]]\n*[[Robert Graves]]\n*Harriet Hyman Alonso\n*[[Etgar Keret]]\n{{Col-break}}\n*[[Maxine Kumin]]\n*[[James Lecesne]]\n*[[Andri Sn\u00e6r Magnason]]\n*[[Charles C. Mann]]\n*[[Innosanto Nagara]]\n*Mark Reibstein\n{{Col-break}}\n*Susan Robeson\n*Laurie Rubin\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Saramago]]\n*Hal Schrieve\n*[[Anne Sexton]]\n*[[Cory Silverberg]]\n{{Col-break}}\n*[[Ronald Takaki]]\n*Eymard Toledo\n*Patrice Vecchione\n*Emma Williams\n*Ed Young\n*[[Howard Zinn]]\n{{Col-break}}\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Award-winning work==\n;Nadia Terranova\n:2019 \u2014 Winner Premio Alassio Centolibri for ''Farewell, Ghosts''<ref>http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cultura/libri/2019/09/02/nadia-terranova-vince-il-premio-alassio_d4b0758a-f447-4488-a67e-753f80709e24.html</ref>\n;Morten D\u00fcrr\n:2017 \u2014 Winner Danish National Illustration Award for ''Zenobia''\n;[[Chavisa Woods]]\n:2017 \u2014 Winner [[Shirley Jackson Award]] for \u201cTake the Way Home That Leads Back to Sullivan Street\u201d in ''Things To Do When You\u2019re Goth in the Country''<ref>https://www.shirleyjacksonawards.org/2017-shirley-jackson-award-winners/</ref>\n;Davide Reviati\n:2017 \u2014 Winner [[Attilio Micheluzzi]] Prize for Best Writing for ''Spit Three Times''\n:2016 \u2014 Winner [[Carlo Boscarato]] Prize for ''Spit Three Times''\n:2016 \u2014 Winner Lo Straniero Prize for ''Spit Three Times'' \n;[[Yasmina Reza]]\n:2016 \u2014 Winner [[Prix Renaudot]] for ''Babylon''\n;[[Annie Ernaux]]\n:2016 \u2014 Winner [[Strega European Prize]] for ''The Years''\n;[[Lola Lafo